<div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code> fontforge.ShowATT.Font: 600 8pt Trebuchet MS  
</code></pre></div></div>

<hr />

<h2 id="display-font---groups">Display Font - Groups</h2>

<ol>
  <li>
    <p>Next we’ll be changing the display font for the ‘Encoding&gt;DisplayByGroups’ and ‘Encoding&gt;DefineGroups’ dialogue boxes, just like we did in the previous steps for Lookups and ShowATT.<br />
<img src="/assets/images/interface/37-change-display-font-fontforge.png" alt="change-display-font-for-groups-in-fontforge" width="70%" height="70%" /></p>

    <p class="note"><strong>Be aware</strong> that within a couple of seconds after opening the ‘DisplayByGroups’ or ‘DefineGroups’ dialogue box, Fontforge crashes on Windows 10. This occurs with the default font and substituted font.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>This is what the default font looks like;<br />
<img src="/assets/images/interface/38-change-display-font-fontforge.png" alt="show-current-display-font-settings" width="30%" height="30%" /></p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>To change it, you’ll need to add a line of code to your personal preferences file. Your changes will appear the next time you open Fontforge.<br />
<img src="/assets/images/interface/39-change-display-font-fontforge.png" alt="you'll-need-to-adding-a-line-of-code-to-your-personal-preferences-file-for-fontforge-user-interface" width="50%" height="50%" /></p>

    <p><strong>Here are some examples:</strong></p>
  </li>
</ol>

<p><img src="/assets/images/interface/40-change-display-font-fontforge-tahoma.png" alt="example-display-font-8pt-tahoma" width="50%" height="50%" /></p>

<div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code> Gdraw.Groups.Font: 400 8pt Tahoma  
</code></pre></div></div>

<hr />

<p><img src="/assets/images/interface/41-change-display-font-fontforge-nirmala.png" alt="example-display-font-10pt-nirmala" width="50%" height="50%" /></p>

<div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code> Gdraw.Groups.Font: 400 10pt Nirmala UI
</code></pre></div></div>

<hr />

<p><img src="/assets/images/interface/42-change-display-font-fontforge-segoe.png" alt="example-display-font-9pt-segoe" width="50%" height="50%" /></p>

<div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code> Gdraw.Groups.Font: 400 9pt Segoe UI  
</code></pre></div></div>

<p><strong>That brings us to the end of this tutorial.</strong></p>

<p>I hope this tutorial has been of assistance and you can put some of the information to good use when using Fontforge.</p>

